<TITLE> Bus crushes biker in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 12 (bdnews24.com) A motorcycle rider was crushed to death under the wheels of a bus on the road at the capital's Moghbazar on Saturday morning. The victim's wife, who was riding with him, was critically injured in the accident, police and witnesses said. They said 36-year old Saiful Huda Shaheen was marketing officer of a private firm. Injured Soheli Akhter Shampa, 30, worked as administration officer at the daily Janakantha, her uncle Bazlur Rahman told bdnews24.com. He said the accident occurred at around 9:30am when a bus of Balaka Paribahan ran over the couple at Moghbazar crossing, killing Shaheen on the spot. Shaheen was taking his wife to her workplace from their house at Rampura Mahanagar Project, Rahman said. Five-month pregnant Soheli was rushed and admitted to Holy Family Hospital, he said. Shaheen's body was sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital morgue for autopsy. bdnew
